-- CCR Authorizes Negotiation to Buy Stakes in Airport Projects
-- B y   A d r i a n a   C h i a r i n i
-- 2011-12-26T22:27:41Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-26/ccr-authorizes-negotiation-to-buy-stakes-in-airport-projects.html
The board of directors of Sao Paulo-
based toll road operator CCR SA authorized its executives to
negotiate the purchase of stakes in airport projects from two
shareholders in CCR, Andrade Gutierrez Participacoes SA and
Camargo Correa SA.  CCR approved a price of $140 million for a stake in an
airport project in Quito, Ecuador, $50 million for a project in
San Jose,  Costa Rica , and $24.5 million for a project in
Curacao, the company said in an e-mailed press release.  To contact the reporter on this story:
